article.headline: Columbia 76, Sacred Heart 71
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- John Baumann and Niko Scott scored 16 points apiece and Columbia rallied for a 76-71 victory over Sacred Heart on Saturday. Justin Armstrong made a 3-pointer and Scott added five points in an 8-0 run that gave the Lions (5-3) a 52-45 lead with 13:59 left. Sacred Heart (2-5) led by one at halftime and 42-38 early in the second half Columbia held its largest lead at 62-53 with 6:50 left but Jarrid Frye scored nine of his 12 points in the final 6 minutes to keep the Pioneers close. Chauncey Hardy led Sacred Heart with 19 points and Joey Henley added 12. Armstrong had eight of his 10 points in the second half.
